// Nightshift Workers interface — the core agent execution contract.
//
// Workers is the load-bearing surface of the Nightshift specification.
// It defines what it means to run an autonomous agent on the control
// plane:
//
//   * Run lifecycle (PENDING -> RUNNING -> COMPLETED / ERROR /
//     INTERRUPTED).
//   * Invoker attribution — every run records `invoker_type` (user or
//     schedule) + `invoker_id` so billing, audit, and quota can
//     distinguish human- from cron-triggered workloads.
//   * Nightshift-owned `session_id` — a control-plane identifier for
//     multi-turn conversations, intentionally distinct from whatever
//     session identifier the agent SDK uses internally. The
//     implementation is responsible for mapping a Nightshift
//     session_id to its SDK-specific state.
//   * Streaming events (`StreamRunEvents`) with history replay, plus
//     a non-streaming history accessor.
//   * Interrupt / cancellation semantics.
//   * Session deletion (`DeleteSession`) — removes all runs and
//     associated session state for a given session_id.
//   * Completion payload carrying cost (USD) and per-model token
//     usage, captured from the agent SDK's terminal message.
//   * Worker callback RPCs — the contract by which the run container
//     posts events and terminal outcomes back to the control plane.
//     These are a separate trust boundary from the user-facing RPCs
//     (§8 of `workers.md`).
//
// Workers persists its durable state through Storage: run metadata as
// `Record`s in the `runs` collection, events as `Record`s in the
// `events` collection (with a (run_id, index) ordering invariant), and
// per-user / per-session SDK state as `Object`s on an implementation-
// defined bucket convention (for example EFS-backed RWX volumes in the
// reference implementation).
//
// Artifact lifecycle events (`artifact.created`, `artifact.updated`,
// `artifact.app_deployed`; see `artifacts.proto`) are forwarded
// through Workers' streaming interface as `StreamEvent`s with
// `type = "artifact.*"`. Subscribers see the same `ArtifactEvent`
// payload that was emitted.

